comments.body:
> I would like to be able to charge image pulling to a pod in the future. I suspect I need the pod sandbox as input.

@derekwaynecarr Could you explain the usecases of  pulling image to a pod? And if image has not beed pulled, what image could be used to create the pod?

I suppose this is not the use-case of docker, hyper or oci-runtime (they all needs the image before creating a pod). So I agree with @yujuhong to add this later.

@derekwaynecarr Thanks. Reasonable. 

> Runtimes that want to innovate in this space are then free to pursue it
> from the start without requiring any version changes etc.

@yujuhong Do you agree add PodSandoxConfig to PullImage now?

@derekwaynecarr I thought our goal is to have a separate service to do the image pulling . And I think the puller can pull images concurrently (https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/25899/files#r64438160)
Then how could you bind the pulling to one pod sandbox's resource restriction?

cc @philips @kubernetes/sig-rktnetes
